properties.name: Miami
properties.description: Visited with my family as well as alone, but I was too young to have seen anything of interest

properties.name: Ocean Ridge
properties.description: Visiting my aunt who lives here

properties.name: Seattle
properties.description: Preparing for PCT and met up with Simon.

properties.name: Harts Pass
properties.description: Hiked up from the road with Simon after being dropped off by our Trail Angel Detour (Bert) who gave us a ride from Arlington. Met Mike, Joe and Tara (Floridian) and a few others I never met again. Arrived late afternoon, left early next morning.

properties.name: Stehekin
properties.description: Reached the town with Simon and Mike at noon and left next day same time. Briefly met Drifter and hiked out with Joe and someone whose name I can't remember, no one saw him after Cascade Locks. Sent back ice axe and long underwear.

properties.name: Steven's Pass
properties.description: Had some issues finding a ride into Skykomish.

properties.name: Skykomish
properties.description: Arrived evening and took a full zero with Simon, Mike and Joe. Stayed at the hotel, laundry in skirt, double dinner.

properties.name: Snoqualmie Pass
properties.description: Arrived around noon, took the day and left following day around noon. Simon's last town before getting a ride back to Seattle by Dan (Aadvark). Met Bucket on the way in. Awesome food and wine. Mediocre pancakes at the Pancake House. New shoes didn't arrive. Left noon next day

properties.name: White Pass
properties.description: Arrived evening, got some leftovers and chips for dinner. Waited an entire day for new shoes to arrive. Mike showed up and we went to packwood after DHL dropped them off. Met my first North Bounder, Legend of all people.

properties.name: Packwood
properties.description: Arrived afternoon with Mike, left early next morning with Cinch and French Fry. Cheapest hotel ever. Nice town.

properties.name: Cascade Locks
properties.description: Met Glue and Brooke whom I missed up by Harts Pass. The day after Goat Rock's Wilderness I met Keith for the first time, met him again as I was eating ice cream in Cascade Locks. Took a zero and a full day.

properties.name: Timberline Lodge
properties.description: Arrived at 11ish, missed breakfast buffet. Great resupply from hiker box.

properties.name: Olallie Lake Resort
properties.description: Arrived for some early breakfast coffee and left after one hour or so.

properties.name: Big Lake Youth Camp
properties.description: Arrived after having a lunch beer with a Trail Angle whose name I can't recall. Scratch knows. Got my resupply package, showered, and left.

properties.name: Elk Lake Resort
properties.description: Arrived too early, no breakfast until 9am or something silly. Waited, charged, ate and left.

properties.name: Shelter Cove Resort
properties.description: Got a care package from Marla.

properties.name: Mazama Village
properties.description: Crater Lake rim trail was closed when I arrived, hitchhiked around and heard it would open the next day. Hitchhiked back and hiked it. Met Connecticut.

properties.name: Callahan's
properties.description: Arrived evening, had dinner and slept in their backyard. Met Connecticut again.

properties.name: Ashland
properties.description: After Callahan's I went into Ashland, and took a full day off. Met Keith and we decided to hike out together the net day.

properties.name: Seiad Valley
properties.description: First poison oak. Arrived late afternoon. Weird place. Left next day after breakfast.

properties.name: Etna
properties.description: Perfect hitch, arrived late afteroon, ate, slept in motel and left early next morning.

properties.name: Castella
properties.description: Nasty gas station area, arrived early evening, got a care package from Ann-Marie, left same night.

properties.name: Burney Falls State Park
properties.description: Bad resupply, arrived and left pretty quickly to the ranch.

properties.name: Burney Mountain Guest Ranch
properties.description: Nice place, dinner, breakfast and spent the next day before night hiking Hat Creek's Rim.

properties.name: Old Station
properties.description: Waited for Keith's package.

properties.name: Drakesbad Guest Ranch
properties.description: Waited for Keith's backpack. Met Sherpa who disappeared on the trail somewhere in Washington.

properties.name: Belden
properties.description: Arrived early, had lunch, left same day. Festival town.

properties.name: Sierra City
properties.description: Arrived early, all restaurants closed, had really expensive ice cream, left same day.

properties.name: Truckee
properties.description: Perfect hitch, had dinner, yuppy marker resupply and went back to the trail to sleep. California girl had her car broken into by a bear.

properties.name: Echo Lake
properties.description: Arrived noon, had ice cream and went into Tahoe.

properties.name: South Lake Tahoe
properties.description: Arrived early afternoon, weird hitchhike guy, took a zero. Changed backpack, new shoes and picked up my tarp again.

properties.name: Kennedy Meadow Resort
properties.description: Met Yakattack on the way, hitchhiked in together and had dinner, 4 ice creams and spent the night stealth camping in their campground. Had birthday breakfast.

properties.name: Tuolumne Meadows
properties.description: Met Machine when he arrived on the bus coming from the Valley. Terrible place to eat. Left early afternoon.

properties.name: Reds Meadow Campground
properties.description: Had lunch, resupplied for a long stretch and left.

properties.name: Independence
properties.description: Arrived early, realized there's nothing in town so took the bus to Lone Pine. Saw Drifter on the way into Independence.

properties.name: Lone Pine
properties.description: Looked for dinner, stayed in a motel and took the bus back the next morning after breakfast.

properties.name: Kennedy Meadows
properties.description: Caught up with drifter and arrived when the store was closed. Last day with breakfast following morning and met Scratch and Machine who hiked with.

properties.name: Lake Isabella
properties.description: Arrived early noon and went back the same afternoon after having resupplied. Hiked with Machine.

properties.name: Tehachapi
properties.description: Had amazing food, slept at Best Western, met Scratch, Machine and Drifter again.

properties.name: Hikertown
properties.description: Arrived after dark, slept and left next morning. Arrived with Scratch and Machine and met Drifter the next morning. Didn't get my resupply package from Ann-Marie but the guy who runs the place drove ahead and left it for me on the trail. Met Cakes.

properties.name: Lake Hughes
properties.description: Trail was closed so walked through Lake Hughes towards Green Valley. Scratch stayed in Green Valley.

properties.name: Agua Dulce
properties.description: Arrived with Drifter and Machine came soon after. Met up with Keith's sister joined in. Had dinner and slept on the rail.

properties.name: Wrightwood
properties.description: Arrived early, had terrible Mexican food, went back on trail the same day. Hiked with Cakes as well.

properties.name: Cajon Pass
properties.description: McDonald's was closed. Had coffee, snacks and continued on.

properties.name: Big Bear Lake
properties.description: Arrived noon, spent the day and big part of the following day. Rented a cabin/house with Keith and his sister. Keith made breakfast. Had indian food. Alexis went back home.

properties.name: Idyllwild
properties.description: Met up with Cakes again. Arrived early, had lunch in the grocery store and left.

properties.name: Warner Springs
properties.description: Picked up my last care package from Ann Marie, continued after having eaten half of it.

properties.name: Julian
properties.description: Met Cakes as she was hitchhiking into town. Had breakfast as well as apple pie and ice cream. Went back on trail after breakfast.

properties.name: Mount Laguna
properties.description: Arrived for breakfast which ended up being ice cream. Keith had an entire refrigerator pie. Met Machine again.

properties.name: Lake Morena
properties.description: Arrived in time for dinner which was amazing. Ate too much. Slept on the trail.

properties.name: Campo
properties.description: Reached the border at 1:50pm together with Daddy Long Legs who I hiked with since Ashland. 2663 miles (4286 km) in 103 days. Only thru-hiker before us was Drifer who arrived the day before. Two other hikers arrived the day before him but they skipped sections up in Washington.

properties.name: Pacific Crest Trail
properties.description: Hiked the entire PCT end-to-end from North to South in 103 days. 2663 miles or 4286 km.

properties.name: New York City
properties.description: Visited the city for a bit before going to Ithaca

properties.name: Ithaca
properties.description: Visited the with Keith

properties.name: Trumansburg
properties.description: Visited the with Keith
